                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am book-keeper to Mr. Wykes; the prisoner at the bar came to enquire for the Northampton coach, he was directed to the Ram inn, in Smithfield, or the Ball and Mouth; he was going out, and I could perceive that he had a parcel in his hand, I called out stop thief, and he immediately dropped the bundle at the door, and ran away; the other witness, 
               <persName id="t18010114-94-person899">
                  William 
